Panda3D is a game engine, a framework for 3D rendering and game development for
Python and C++ programs. Panda3D is open-source and free for any purpose,
including commercial ventures, thanks to its liberal license. To learn more
about Panda3D's capabilities, visit the gallery and the feature list. To learn
how to use Panda3D, check the documentation resources. If you get stuck, ask for
help from our active community.

Panda3D is licensed under the Modified BSD License. See the LICENSE file for
more details.
